{"data":[{"type":"questionAttempts","id":"17491423","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionAttempts/17491423"},"attributes":{"position":0,"marks":1,"score":1,"answeredAt":"2025-09-29T05:46:28+09:30","options":[1],"response":null,"finalizedAt":"2025-09-29T05:46:28+09:30"},"relationships":{"user":{"data":{"type":"users","id":"50098"}},"questionSession":{"data":null},"session":{"data":null},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"934"}},"bookmark":{"data":null}}}],"included":[{"type":"questions","id":"934","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questions/934"},"attributes":{"optionProportions":[0.17,0.72,0.03,0.04,0.04]},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"934"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"83495"}}}},{"type":"items","id":"934","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/items/934"},"attributes":{"contentType":"question"},"relationships":{"content":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"934"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"68368"}},"tags":{"data":[{"type":"tags","id":"19"},{"type":"tags","id":"25"},{"type":"tags","id":"35"},{"type":"tags","id":"65"},{"type":"tags","id":"71"},{"type":"tags","id":"76"},{"type":"tags","id":"549"},{"type":"tags","id":"1181"},{"type":"tags","id":"1217"},{"type":"tags","id":"2058"},{"type":"tags","id":"4959"},{"type":"tags","id":"11637"},{"type":"tags","id":"11644"}]},"contributions":{"data":[{"type":"contributions","id":"252"},{"type":"contributions","id":"5028"},{"type":"contributions","id":"10758"},{"type":"contributions","id":"28371"},{"type":"contributions","id":"44487"},{"type":"contributions","id":"44928"}]}},"meta":{"canRevise":false,"canManage":false,"canDelete":false}},{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"83495","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionRevisions/83495"},"attributes":{"stem":"\u003Cp\u003EAn otherwise well 35-year-old man presents to the General Practice clinic with a two-week history of a painless swelling in his neck. On examination, there is a well-defined, 4 cm diameter, smooth-surfaced swelling immediately superior to the thyroid cartilage. The skin moves freely over the swelling. There is elevation of the swelling when the patient protrudes his tongue.\u003C/p\u003E","stemQuestion":"Which one of the following is the most appropriate initial investigation?","responseType":"sba","marks":1,"options":["Thyroid function tests","Ultrasound scan","View under laryngoscopy","CT Imaging","Fine needle aspiration"],"correctOptions":[1],"correctResponses":null,"explanation":"\u003Cp\u003EFrom the clinical description, this patient most likely has a thyroglossal duct cyst. Whilst not common, these cysts are seen more often than other congenital neck masses. Whilst they normally present during childhood, thyroglossal cysts may not become apparent until the patient is in their 20s or 30s. They may present as a simple swelling or pain, if infection within the cyst occurs. The diagnosis can rapidly and simply be confirmed with \u003Cstrong\u003Eultrasound\u003C/strong\u003E. If there are any atypical features (e.g., a solid component), then \u003Cstrong\u003ECT\u003C/strong\u003E or \u003Cstrong\u003EMR\u003C/strong\u003E imaging may be needed to define an orthotopic thyroid gland or to exclude malignancy. \u003Cstrong\u003EFine needle aspiration\u003C/strong\u003E is a useful diagnostic tool for evaluation but it is not a suitable initial investigation considering its invasive nature and its risks involved. \u003Cstrong\u003EView under laryngoscopy\u003C/strong\u003E is commonly performed to assess the upper airway and laryngeal structures for abnormalities such as vocal cord nodules, polyps, cysts, tumors, and inflammation, and to assess vocal cord mobility. It may not provide detailed information about the nature of the neck swelling itself.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EIf it was thought that the swelling originated from within the thyroid gland, then \u003Cstrong\u003Ethyroid function tests\u003C/strong\u003E might be appropriate. However, the clinical description of a midline swelling immediately superior to the thyroid cartilage, moving up when the tongue is protruded is diagnostic of a thyroglossal cyst.\u003C/p\u003E","optionExplanations":["","","","",""],"learningPoints":["Ultrasound imaging is the preferred investigation for most superficial isolated swellings.","Thyroglossal duct cysts typically present as midline neck swellings that move with tongue protrusion."],"references":["Patel S, Bhatt AA. Thyroglossal dct pathology and mimics. Insights Imaging 2019; 10:12.Patel S, Bhatt AA. Thyroglossal duct pathology and mimics. Insights Imaging. 2019 Feb 6;10(1):12. doi: 10.1186/s13244-019-0694-x. PMID: 30725193; PMCID: PMC6365310. Avaialble from: https://pubmed.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/30725193/","Patigaroo SA, Dar NH, Jallu AS, Ahmad R. Thyroglossal Duct Cysts: A Clinicosurgical Experience. Indian J Otolaryngol Head Neck Surg. 2017 Mar;69(1):102-107. doi: 10.1007/s12070-016-1029-6. Epub 2016 Oct 27. PMID: 28239589; PMCID: PMC5305636. Available from: https://pmc.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/articles/PMC5305636/","Amos J, Shermetaro C. Thyroglossal Duct Cyst. [Updated 2023 Jun 26]. In: StatPearls [Internet]. Treasure Island (FL): StatPearls Publishing; 2025 Jan-. Available from: https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/books/NBK519057/"]},"relationships":{"itemRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"68368"}},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"934"}},"stemMedia":{"data":[]},"explanationMedia":{"data":[]}}},{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"68368","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/itemRevisions/68368"},"attributes":{"createdAt":"2025-02-04T20:20:48+10:30","updatedAt":"2025-02-04T20:23:50+10:30"},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"934"}},"content":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"83495"}}},"meta":{"canDelete":false}},{"type":"tags","id":"19","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/19"},"attributes":{"emoji":"\ud83d\ud